body.stringValue:
The purpose of Christian philosophy is to use reason to make religious convictions clear, and to identify eternal truth. Christian philosophers use their faith in cosmology and everyday life to guide their work. They also use philosophy to promote their faith, and to answer questions about reality, the good life, and how to be a good person.
